      <section eId="sec_CHC-1188">
        <num>CHC 1188</num>
        <heading>1188.  Motion for disclosure</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1188__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>An adopted person or, if still a minor, his legal representative on his behalf may
file a motion for disclosure of information pertaining to his adoption pursuant to Article
1189.  The action shall be styled: &quot;In re the Adoption of _____________&quot;.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1188__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A biological sibling or descendant of an adopted person, or if still a minor, his
legal representative on his behalf, may file a motion for disclosure pursuant to Article 1189.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1188__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>This action, the limited medical exception provision of Article 1127, and the
provisions of R.S. 40:73, 77, and 79 shall be the exclusive means for gaining access to
records of adoptions whether maintained by this court, some other court, an adoption agency,
any state agency, or private individual, notwithstanding provisions of law to the contrary.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72660</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
